  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "M&E Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>To coordinate M&E design matters with Consultants and Sub-contractors and to resolve any technical\nissues.</li><li>To prepare method statement, shop drawings, installation and T&C check list, work progress report and other relevant documents for M&E related works with the project team.</li><li>To establish the M&E work program based on the Master Program, and to ensure M&E works are carried\nout on timely manner.</li><li>To ensure M&E works are carried out according to specifications/design drawings.</li><li>To inform the M&E Manager of any technical / site problems pertaining to M&E works.</li><li>To liaise and hold meetings with M&E consultants on technical resolution and inspection.</li><li>To ensure the quality of works to be achieved and safety regulations are complied with.</li><li>To be responsible for general on-site technical difficulties and other problems that may arise.</li><li>To prepare and compile the As-built document (Drawings, Handover Document, Inspection records etc) by working with the project team and subcons</li><li>Project planning, site investigation, preliminary design and cost estimation on mechanical and electrical works for the new tender project.</li><li>To prepare tender queries by studying the tender drawings and specifications.</li><li>To review and evaluate subcontractor’s quotation and prices.</li><li>To create a Value Engineering and Cost Saving proposal to match the client’s requirements.</li><li>Any other duties as assigned.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Candidate must possess at least a Degree/Diploma in Engineering (Electrical), Engineering (Mechanical) or\nEquivalent</li><li>At least 2 years of working experience in building construction for this position.</li><li>Familiar with construction site activities.</li><li>Basic computer skills for Microsoft Office and AutoCAD</li><li>Hospital, Nursing home or Healthcare project experience.</li><li>Warehouse or Factory project experience.</li><li>Positive working attitude and ability to work in a team</li><li>Preference for working experiences overseas, such as in other South East Asia or Japan</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 2,
